=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Use enantiopure (R)-glycidyl methyl ether and open the epoxide with NaN3/NH4Cl to give (R)-MeOCH2CH(OH)CH2N3; then trap the alcohol with phenyl isocyanate to form the carbamate (R)-MeOCH2CH(OC(O)NHPh)CH2N3. | Step 2: Reduce the azide (H2/Pd-C or PPh3/H2O) to obtain the key chiral amine (R)-MeOCH2CH(OC(O)NHPh)CH2NH2. | Step 3: In a convergent branch, prepare 4-bromobutyl sulfonamide electrophile by 1,4-dibromobutane + potassium phthalimide -> Br(CH2)4NPhth, hydrazinolysis -> H2N(CH2)4Br, then sulfonylation with 2,4-dichlorobenzenesulfonyl chloride to give Br(CH2)4NHSO2(c1ccc(Cl)cc1Cl). | Step 4: Alkylate the Step 2 amine with Br(CH2)4NHSO2(2,4-dichlorophenyl) (K2CO3 or DIPEA) to form the secondary amine MeOCH2CH(OC(O)NHPh)CH2NH(CH2)4NHSO2(2,4-dichlorophenyl). | Step 5: Carbamoylate that secondary amine with isopropyl isocyanate to furnish the target COC[C@@H](CN(CCCCNS(=O)(=O)c1ccc(Cl)cc1Cl)C(=O)NC(C)C)OC(=O)Nc1ccccc1.

